<item>
            <title>[LU-6253] Document All Tests Done in Test Scripts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6253</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In many of our test plans and demonstration documents, we just refer to the running of specific test scripts (i.e. sanity_dne.sh).  This does not help the reader understand what is actually being tested by the test script unless the reader wants to read the bash script&apos;s comments and code to determine what is being tested.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should have a single, maintained description of what is tested by each test script.  Preferably this description is versioned so we can refer to a version of the script&apos;s description from test plans and demonstration documents.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
